sql:
SELECT project_id, feature_id, AVG(usage_duration) AS avg_usage_duration
FROM application_usage
GROUP BY project_id, feature_id;

external_knowledge:
- Cost variance is calculated as (actual cost - total resource cost) / budget;
- A project is considered "ongoing" if its status is 'IN PROGRESS';
- A milestone is a significant point or event in the project timeline;
- The total resource cost is the sum of all resource costs associated with the project, excluding any currency symbols and commas.

- "nurtured their projects to a point where at least half of the milestones have blossomed" refers to projects where at least 50% of the milestones are completed;
- "gardeners (developers)" and "caretakers (testers)" refer to the roles of team members in the project;
- "tend to at least two milestones or features" refers to team members being assigned to at least 2 milestones or features.

